label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Staging of eyelid carcinoma begins with a comprehensive ophthalmic, orbital, and periorbital clinical examination.  This approach includes a slit lamp or equivalent biomicroscopy evaluation, neuro-ophthalmic examination for evidence of perineural invasion, and regional assessment of the head and neck including lymphatic drainage basins. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Clinical Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid cNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid cN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with no regional lymph node metastasis, based upon clinical evaluation or imaging. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid cN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Refractory Follicular Lymphoma

value.value: Follicular lymphoma grade I, II, III that is resistant to treatment.

label.value: Gantenerumab

value.value: A monoclonal antibody against beta-amyloid (Abeta40/42) used in the treatment of Alzheimer's disease. Gantenerumab targets and binds to beta amyloid then is removed through effector cell-mediated clearance. This reduces the level of beta amyloid in the brain. In Alzheimer's disease, beta amyloid accumulates in the brain and is a key component in plaque formation.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the eyelid, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Eyelid cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the eyelid with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Motavizumab

value.value: A humanized monoclonal antibody directed against the respiratory syncytial virus (RSV) fusion glycoprotein (F-protein), with activity against RSV. Motavizumab targets and binds to the RSV F-protein, which prevents F-protein-mediated RSV fusion with human host cells. This protects against RSV infection. RSV F-protein mediates RSV attachment and fusion to host cells.

label.value: Solanezumab

value.value: A humanized monoclonal antibody (IgG1) raised against amyloid beta peptides with Alzheimer disease treatment application. Solanezumab recognizes and binds the middle amino acid residues 16-24 of the amyloid beta peptide and may be used in a passive immunotherapy treatment.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  No stage grouping is presently recommended for carcinoma of the conjunctiva.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete resection of the primary site is indicated (if possible).  The specimen should be thoroughly sampled for histologic study of surgical margins, type of tumor, and grade of malignancy.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Pathologic Primary Tumor TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pTX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage I Follicular Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage I: Involvement of a single lymph node region (I); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in the absence of any lymph node involvement (IE).

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pTis TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with a finding of carcinoma in situ. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor measuring 5 mm or less in greatest dimension.  Note: tumors occur most commonly in the bulbar limbal conjunctiva. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT2 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor measuring more than 5 mm in greatest dimension without invasion of adjacent structures.  Adjacent structures include the cornea (3, 6, 9, or 12 clock hours), intraocular compartments, forniceal conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), palpebral conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), tarsal conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), lacrimal punctum and canaliculi (lower and/or upper), plica, caruncle, posterior eyelid lamella, anterior eyelid lamella, and/or eyelid margin (lower and/or upper).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Benralizumab

value.value: An afucosylated, humanized monoclonal antibody against the alpha chain of the interleukin-5 receptor (IL-5Ra), with potential anti-asthmatic activity. Upon administration, benralizumab binds to IL-5Ra and elicits an antibody-directed cell cytotoxicity (ADCC) against IL-5Ra-expressing cells. This induces apoptosis in IL-5Ra-expressing cells and may reduce asthmatic episodes. IL-5Ra, expressed on both eosinophils and basophils, plays a key role in asthma.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT3 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading adjacent structures (excluding the orbit).  Adjacent structures include the cornea (3, 6, 9, or 12 clock hours), intraocular compartments, forniceal conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), palpebral conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), tarsal conjunctiva (lower and/or upper), lacrimal punctum and canaliculi (lower and/or upper), plica, caruncle, posterior eyelid lamella, anterior eyelid lamella, and/or eyelid margin (lower and/or upper).  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT4 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading the orbit with or without further extension. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT4a TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading the orbital soft tissues, without bone invasion. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT4b TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading bone. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT4c TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading adjacent paranasal sinuses. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Thyroid Hormone

value.value: Any of several closely related compounds that are produced by the thyroid gland and are active metabolically.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage II Follicular Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage II: Involvement of two or more lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (II); or localized involvement of a single extralymphatic organ or site in association with regional lymph node involvement with or without involvement of other lymph node regions on the same side of the diaphragm (IIE).

label.value: Tenatumomab
Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pT4d TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with tumor invading the brain. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Pathologic Regional Lymph Nodes TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of regional lymph nodes.

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pNX TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva in which the regional lymph nodes cannot be assessed.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pN0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with no regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pN1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with regional lymph node metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Pathologic Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.  There is no pathologic M0 for carcinoma of the conjunctiva. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva pM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Clinical TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  The assessment of cancer is based on inspection, slit-lamp examination, and palpation of the regional lymph nodes.  All conjunctival surfaces are inspected and photographed with eversion of the upper eyelid.  High-frequency ultrasound (UBM) imaging should be performed when the tumor is found to be affixed to the globe and when intraocular invasion is suspected.  Low-frequency ultrasound may also be used to evaluate the sclera, eye, and orbit. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva Clinical Distant Metastasis TNM Finding v7

value.value: A clinical finding about one or more characteristics of carcinoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to distant metastases.

label.value: Ann Arbor Stage III Follicular Lymphoma

value.value: Ann Arbor Classification: Stage III: Involvement of lymph node regions on both sides of the diaphragm (III), which also may be accompanied by extralymphatic extension in association with adjacent lymph node involvement (IIIE) or by involvement of the spleen (IIIS) or both (IIIE,S).

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva cM0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva without evidence of distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Carcinoma of the Conjunctiva cM1 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Carcinoma of the conjunctiva with distant metastasis. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Ibalizumab

value.value: A humanized monoclonal antibody against CD4, with anti-human immunodeficiency virus (HIV) activity. Ibalizumab binds to CD4, the primary receptor for HIV, thereby inhibiting HIV entry into CD4-positive T-cells. This leads to a reduction in viral load.

label.value: Melanoma of the Conjunctiva TNM Finding v7

value.value: A finding about one or more characteristics of melanoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  No stage grouping is presently recommended for melanoma of the conjunctiva.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Melanoma of the Conjunctiva Pathologic TNM Finding v7

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of melanoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system.  Complete resection of the primary site is indicated. Histopathologic evaluation for negative peripheral and deep margins should be performed.  To best judge the depth of penetration of the tumor, sections should be made perpendicular to the epithelial surface.  (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

value.value: A pathologic finding about one or more characteristics of melanoma of the conjunctiva, following the rules of the TNM AJCC v7 classification system as they pertain to staging of the primary tumor.

value.value: Melanoma of the conjunctiva in which the primary tumor cannot be assessed. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)

label.value: Melanoma of the Conjunctiva pT0 TNM Finding v7

value.value: Melanoma of the conjunctiva with no evidence of a primary tumor. (from AJCC 7th Ed.)
